UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1988
1 AN ACT relating to disabled veterans.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 40 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Accessibility ramp" means a modular or custom-built ramp, including
7 appurtenant parts thereto such as landings and railings, all of which are:
8 1. Constructed in accordance with and otherwise comply with all
9 pertinent parts of the federal Americans with Disabilities Act, 42
10 U.S.C. sec. 12101 et seq.; the Kentucky Residential Building Code
11 adopted under KRS Chapter 198B; any local government ordinances;
12 and any homeowners association covenants; and
13 2. Constructed and installed by a contractor or other person registered
14 with the Kentucky Secretary of State and whose business would
15 encompass the construction and installation of accessibility ramps;
16 (b) "Disabled veteran" means an individual, domiciled in Kentucky, who has
17 served in the Armed Forces, has been separated therefrom under honorable
18 or general conditions, and has established the present existence of a service-
19 connected disability or is receiving compensation, disability retirements
20 benefits, or pension because of a public statute administered by the United
21 States Department of Veterans Affairs or Department of Defense, or was
22 separated by the Department of Defense because of a disability;
23 (c) "Immediate family member" means a disabled veteran's father, mother,
24 brother, sister, spouse, son, daughter, stepson, stepdaughter, grandchild,
25 aunt, uncle, son-in-law, or daughter-in-law; and
26 (d) "Residence" means a single-family home owned by a disabled veteran or an
27 immediate family member of a disabled veteran which is the principal place
Page 1 of 2
