UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1988
1 of residence of the disabled veteran.
2 (2) There is established in the Kentucky Department of Veterans' Affairs the
3 Residential Ease of Access for Disabled Veterans Program for the purpose of
4 funding the construction and installation of accessibility ramps on residences of
5 disabled veterans.
6 (3) In developing an application procedure, the Kentucky Department of Veterans'
7 Affairs shall require persons applying to the program for the construction and
8 installation of an accessibility ramp for a disabled veteran to first contact the
9 nearest veterans' service organization which shall then transmit applications to
10 the department.
11 (4) There is hereby established in the State Treasury a trust and agency account to be
12 known as the Residential Ease of Access for Disabled Veterans Program grant
13 fund, which shall consist of moneys received from state appropriations, gifts,
14 grants, and federal funds.
15 (5) The fund shall be administered by the Kentucky Department of Veterans' Affairs.
16 (6) Amounts deposited in the fund shall be used for the purposes set forth in
17 subsection (2) of this section.
18 (7) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, fund amounts not expended at the close of a fiscal
19 year shall not lapse but shall be carried forward into the next fiscal year.
20 (8) The Kentucky Department of Veterans' Affairs may promulgate administrative
21 regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A to implement this section.
